verses.text_plain: Moreover he said unto me, Son of man, eat that thou findest; eat this roll, and go speak unto the house of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 1Moreover he said unto me, Son of man, eat that thou findest; eat this roll, and go speak unto the house of Israel.

verses.text_plain: So I opened my mouth, and he caused me to eat that roll.
verses.verse_html: 2So I opened my mouth, and he caused me to eat that roll.

tokens.text: and he caused me to eat

verses.text_plain: And he said unto me, Son of man, cause thy belly to eat, and fill thy bowels with this roll that I give thee. Then did I eat it; and it was in my mouth as honey for sweetness.
verses.verse_html: 3And he said unto me, Son of man, cause thy belly to eat, and fill thy bowels with this roll that I give thee. Then did I eat it; and it was in my mouth as honey for sweetness.

tokens.text: and it was in my mouth

verses.text_plain: And he said unto me, Son of man, go, get thee unto the house of Israel, and speak with my words unto them.
verses.verse_html: 4And he said unto me, Son of man, go, get thee unto the house of Israel, and speak with my words unto them.

verses.text_plain: For thou art not sent to a people of a strange speech and of an hard language, but to the house of Israel;
verses.verse_html:
5For thou art not sent to a people of a strange speech and of an hard language, but to the house of Israel; ▼
▼ of a…: Heb. deep of lip, and heavy of tongue

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of a…: Heb. deep of lip, and heavy of tongue
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of a…: Heb. deep of lip, and heavy of tongue

verses.text_plain: Not to many people of a strange speech and of an hard language, whose words thou canst not understand. Surely, had I sent thee to them, they would have hearkened unto thee.
verses.verse_html:
6Not to many people of a strange speech and of an hard language, whose words thou canst not understand. Surely, had I sent thee to them, they would have hearkened unto thee. ▼
▼ of a…: Heb. deep of lip, and heavy of language

verses.text_plain: But the house of Israel will not hearken unto thee; for they will not hearken unto me: for all the house of Israel are impudent and hardhearted.
verses.verse_html:
7But the house of Israel will not hearken unto thee; for they will not hearken unto me: for all the house of Israel are impudent and hardhearted. ▼
▼ impudent…: Heb. stiff of forehead, and hard of heart

footnotes.body_text: ▼ impudent…: Heb. stiff of forehead, and hard of heart
footnotes.body_html: ▼ impudent…: Heb. stiff of forehead, and hard of heart

verses.text_plain: Behold, I have made thy face strong against their faces, and thy forehead strong against their foreheads.
verses.verse_html: 8Behold, I have made thy face strong against their faces, and thy forehead strong against their foreheads.

verses.text_plain: As an adamant harder than flint have I made thy forehead: fear them not, neither be dismayed at their looks, though they be a rebellious house.
verses.verse_html: 9As an adamant harder than flint have I made thy forehead: fear them not, neither be dismayed at their looks, though they be a rebellious house.

verses.text_plain: Moreover he said unto me, Son of man, all my words that I shall speak unto thee receive in thine heart, and hear with thine ears.
verses.verse_html: 10Moreover he said unto me, Son of man, all my words that I shall speak unto thee receive in thine heart, and hear with thine ears.

verses.text_plain: And go, get thee to them of the captivity, unto the children of thy people, and speak unto them, and tell them, Thus saith the Lord God; whether they will hear, or whether they will forbear.
verses.verse_html: 11And go, get thee to them of the captivity, unto the children of thy people, and speak unto them, and tell them, Thus saith the Lord God; whether they will hear, or whether they will forbear.

tokens.text: thee to them of the captivity

verses.text_plain: Then the spirit took me up, and I heard behind me a voice of a great rushing, saying, Blessed be the glory of the Lord from his place.
verses.verse_html: 12Then the spirit took me up, and I heard behind me a voice of a great rushing, saying, Blessed be the glory of the Lord from his place.

verses.text_plain: I heard also the noise of the wings of the living creatures that touched one another, and the noise of the wheels over against them, and a noise of a great rushing.
verses.verse_html:
13I heard also the noise of the wings of the living creatures that touched one another, and the noise of the wheels over against them, and a noise of a great rushing. ▼
▼ touched: Heb. kissed

verses.text_plain: So the spirit lifted me up, and took me away, and I went in bitterness, in the heat of my spirit; but the hand of the Lord was strong upon me.
verses.verse_html:
14So the spirit lifted me up, and took me away, and I went in bitterness, in the heat of my spirit; but the hand of the Lord was strong upon me. ▼
▼ in bitterness: Heb. bitter
 , ▼
▼ heat: Heb. hot anger

verses.text_plain: Then I came to them of the captivity at Tel–abib, that dwelt by the river of Chebar, and I sat where they sat, and remained there astonished among them seven days.
verses.verse_html: 15Then I came to them of the captivity at Tel–abib, that dwelt by the river of Chebar, and I sat where they sat, and remained there astonished among them seven days.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass at the end of seven days, that the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 16And it came to pass at the end of seven days, that the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

tokens.text: And it came to pass at the end

verses.text_plain: Son of man, I have made thee a watchman unto the house of Israel: therefore hear the word at my mouth, and give them warning from me.
verses.verse_html: 17Son of man, I have made thee a watchman unto the house of Israel: therefore hear the word at my mouth, and give them warning from me.

verses.text_plain: When I say unto the wicked, Thou shalt surely die; and thou givest him not warning, nor speakest to warn the wicked from his wicked way, to save his life; the same wicked man shall die in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at thine hand.
verses.verse_html: 18When I say unto the wicked, Thou shalt surely die; and thou givest him not warning, nor speakest to warn the wicked from his wicked way, to save his life; the same wicked man shall die in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at thine hand.

tokens.text: and thou givest him not warning

verses.text_plain: Yet if thou warn the wicked, and he turn not from his wickedness, nor from his wicked way, he shall die in his iniquity; but thou hast delivered thy soul.
verses.verse_html: 19Yet if thou warn the wicked, and he turn not from his wickedness, nor from his wicked way, he shall die in his iniquity; but thou hast delivered thy soul.

verses.text_plain: Again, When a righteous man doth turn from his righteousness, and commit iniquity, and I lay a stumblingblock before him, he shall die: because thou hast not given him warning, he shall die in his sin, and his righteousness which he hath done shall not be remembered; but his blood will I require at thine hand.
verses.verse_html:
20Again, When a righteous man doth turn from his righteousness, and commit iniquity, and I lay a stumblingblock before him, he shall die: because thou hast not given him warning, he shall die in his sin, and his righteousness which he hath done shall not be remembered; but his blood will I require at thine hand. ▼
▼ righteousness which: Heb. righteousnesses

tokens.text: because thou hast not given him warning

footnotes.body_html: ▼ righteousness which: Heb. righteousnesses

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless if thou warn the righteous man, that the righteous sin not, and he doth not sin, he shall surely live, because he is warned; also thou hast delivered thy soul.
verses.verse_html: 21Nevertheless if thou warn the righteous man, that the righteous sin not, and he doth not sin, he shall surely live, because he is warned; also thou hast delivered thy soul.

tokens.text: not, and he doth not sin

verses.text_plain: And the hand of the Lord was there upon me; and he said unto me, Arise, go forth into the plain, and I will there talk with thee.
verses.verse_html: 22And the hand of the Lord was there upon me; and he said unto me, Arise, go forth into the plain, and I will there talk with thee.

tokens.text: was there upon me; and he said

verses.text_plain: Then I arose, and went forth into the plain: and, behold, the glory of the Lord stood there, as the glory which I saw by the river of Chebar: and I fell on my face.
verses.verse_html: 23Then I arose, and went forth into the plain: and, behold, the glory of the Lord stood there, as the glory which I saw by the river of Chebar: and I fell on my face.

verses.text_plain: Then the spirit entered into me, and set me upon my feet, and spake with me, and said unto me, Go, shut thyself within thine house.
verses.verse_html: 24Then the spirit entered into me, and set me upon my feet, and spake with me, and said unto me, Go, shut thyself within thine house.

verses.text_plain: But thou, O son of man, behold, they shall put bands upon thee, and shall bind thee with them, and thou shalt not go out among them:
verses.verse_html: 25But thou, O son of man, behold, they shall put bands upon thee, and shall bind thee with them, and thou shalt not go out among them:

tokens.text: thee with them, and thou shalt not go out

verses.text_plain: And I will make thy tongue cleave to the roof of thy mouth, that thou shalt be dumb, and shalt not be to them a reprover: for they are a rebellious house.
verses.verse_html:
26And I will make thy tongue cleave to the roof of thy mouth, that thou shalt be dumb, and shalt not be to them a reprover: for they are a rebellious house. ▼
